ginal oral testimonies– to explore the challenges and pleasures of conducting research in this field. Containing twelve new essays from an international group of leading and emerging scholars, the book explores and assesses the current status and shape of the field of historical audience research, showcasing new research which foregrounds the transnational and multi-cultural dimensions of past cinemagoing, the roles played by management personnel and marketing campaigns, and the currently under-explored area of the past reception of home video.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMotion picture audiencesxHistory. 0aMotion picture audiencesxResearchxMethodology. 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh1 aAveyard, Karina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBiltereyst, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEgan, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEgan, Kate, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFuhrmann, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarofalo, Damiano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJames, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKuhn, Annette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPenati, Cecilia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPryt, Karina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShail, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmith, Adrian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSm